50|$|However, {{other critics}} state {{that such a}} market would only {{increase}} already high prices for organs, creating an imbalance: only wealthy individuals {{would be able to}} purchase these organs. They also argue that such a free market system for <b>organ</b> <b>trade</b> would encourage <b>organ</b> theft through murder and neglect of sick individuals for financial gain. Advocates for the free market of organs counter these claims by saying that murder for financial gain already happens; sanctions against such acts exist to minimize their occurrence; and with proper regulation and law enforcement, such incidents in a legal <b>organ</b> <b>trade</b> could be minimized as well.|$|R
