25|$|Legalization of the <b>organ</b> <b>trade</b> {{carries with}} it its own sense of justice as well. Continuing black-market trade creates further {{disparity}} on the demand side: only the rich can afford such organs. Legalization of the international <b>organ</b> <b>trade</b> could lead to increased supply, lowering prices so that persons outside the wealthiest segments could afford such organs as well.|$|R
