50|$|In May 2007 the Regulation on Human Organ Transplantation {{came into}} force, banning <b>organ</b> <b>trading</b> and {{the removal of}} a person's organs without their prior written consent, and this has been favourably {{received}} by the World Health Organization and The Transplantation Society. To curb illegal transplants, doctors involved in commercial <b>trade</b> of <b>organs</b> will face fines and suspensions; only a few hospitals will be certified to perform organ transplants. As a result of a systematic overhaul, the number of institutions approved for transplants has been reduced from more than 600 in 2007 to 87 as at October 2008; another 77 have received provisional approval from the Ministry of Health.|$|R
